{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"07a335c9-706b-4aea-abfd-7357c0e68fe9","content":"Here's a quick overview:\n\n**Templates** (most common):\n| Framework | Command |\n|-----------|---------|\n| ASP.NET Core | `dotnet new webapi` |\n| Node/Express | `npx express-generator` |\n| Python/FastAPI | `pip install fastapi` |\n| Python/Flask | `pip install flask` |\n\n**Authentication options for `dotnet new webapi`:**\n- `--auth None` – No auth (default)\n- `--auth Individual` – ASP.NET Identity (local accounts)\n- `--auth IndividualB2C` – Azure AD B2C\n- `--auth SingleOrg` – Azure AD (single tenant)\n- `--auth MultiOrg` – Azure AD (multi-tenant)\n- `--auth Windows` – Windows/Negotiate auth\n\n**For Node/Python**, auth is typically added via libraries:\n- **JWT** – `jsonwebtoken` (Node), `PyJWT` / `python-jose` (Python)\n- **OAuth2/OIDC** – `passport.js` (Node), `authlib` (Python)\n- **API keys** – middleware-based\n\nWould you like me to scaffold a specific project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"af3e9a47-4dec-466a-8ad3-d0eb1936e487","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":335},"id":"6541347e-9cc5-4f3f-b256-63354cc5773e","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:48:20.268Z","parentId":"0074a554-5791-4e62-9983-2b3bc07cd567"}
